sentences: Haruka Tomatsu (戸松 遥, Tomatsu Haruka, born February 4, 1990) is a Japanese voice actress and singer, employed by Music Ray'n.

She plays Asuna in Sword Art Online, Mileina Vashti in Mobile Suit Gundam 00 Second Season, Walther WA 2000 and M4A1 in Girls' Frontline, Aoba Tsukishima in Cross Game, Saki Rukino in Valvrave the Liberator, Lala Satalin Deviluke in To Love Ru, Minamoto no Raikou in Fate/Grand Order, Iona Hikawa/Cure Fortune in HappinessCharge PreCure!, Zero Two in Darling in the Franxx and Haru Okumura in Persona 5.
Tomatsu began a singing career in 2008, performing the song "Naissance" which was used as the ending theme to the television drama series Here Is Greenwood.
In 2009, she became part of the music unit Sphere, alongside Aki Toyosaki, Minako Kotobuki and Ayahi Takagaki.
She released her first album Rainbow Road in 2010, and two compilation albums in 2016.
She released her first album Rainbow Road in 2010, and two compilation albums in 2016.
Her voice acting career began when she participated in an audition held by Sony Music Entertainment Japan subsidiary Music Ray'n from 2005 to 2006.
In January 2006, she participated in the Tōhō Cinderella audition held by Tōhō Entertainment.
Tomatsu made her voice acting debut in 2007, playing a student in Gakuen Utopia Manabi Straight!.
After graduating from high school, Tomatsu moved to Tokyo in 2008 to go to university and to continue her voice acting career.
In 2012, Tomatsu played Asuna Yuuki in Sword Art Online.
In 2013, she received the Best Supporting Actress Award at the 7th Seiyu Awards, and the Synergy Award for her role in Yo-Kai Watch at the 9th Seiyu Awards.

In 2018, she appeared as herself in the television drama series Koe Girl!, which featured her as a voice actress taking care of the series' main characters; the series also featured footage from one of her concerts.
In 2021 she played Kyoko Hori in Hori-san to Miyamura-kun.
"Naissance", her first single, was released on September 3, 2008.

In 2009, Music Ray'n formed the music unit Sphere, which consists of Tomatsu, Aki Toyosaki, Minako Kotobuki and Ayahi Takagaki.

This was followed by her fifth single "Girls, Be Ambitious", which was released on February 8, 2010; the title track is used as the ending theme to the anime series Sound of the Sky.

In July 2016, as part of Sphere, she made her North American live debut at Anime Expo.
Her seventeenth single "Monokuro/Two of Us" (モノクロ/Two of us) was released on November 7, 2016; the song "Two of Us" is used as the theme song to the video game Sword Art Online: Hollow Realization.
Her eighteenth single, "Uchōten Traveller" (有頂天トラベラー), was released on October 23, 2017; the title track is used as the ending theme to the anime series PriPri Chi-chan!!.
She released her fourth solo album Colorful Gift on May 14, 2018.
Her 18th single "Try & Joy" was released on September 5, 2018.

Her 19th single "Resolution" was released digitally on October 13, 2019, and received a physical release on November 20, 2019; the title song is used as the third opening theme to the anime series Sword Art Online: Alicization.

Tomatsu announced her marriage to a non-celebrity man on her blog on January 11, 2019.
She announced the birth of her first child, a girl, on February 9, 2021.
